05:35.533 --> 05:37.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and rewrite them.

05:37.566 --> 05:41.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And what does
a story in the end have to
have to be successful, to work

05:41.466 --> 05:43.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for you?

05:43.600 --> 05:47.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAVID SEDARIS: It used
to be about just racking
up laughs, right? But
I think you need, like,

05:49.733 --> 05:54.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
some sorrow to give the laughter
a bit of weight. And that's
when you remember things.

05:57.100 --> 05:59.133 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
Or that's when I
remember things.

05:59.133 --> 06:03.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So people come
and they want - - you think
they want laughter, but you want

06:05.233 --> 06:08.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
something more. You want
to give them something
more. What is that more?

06:08.466 --> 06:13.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID SEDARIS: I want to
connect with them. I want them
to -- usually, it's the worst

06:15.466 --> 06:19.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
thing you can admit about
yourself that most people
can relate to. Right?

06:21.400 --> 06:24.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was so surprising to me when
I realized that, that when I
thought, well, if you write

06:26.766 --> 06:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about, say, your own jealousy,
people aren't going to think,
oh, he's a horrible person

06:33.166 --> 06:36.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because he's jealous. They
will think, that's me.

06:36.733 --> 06:41.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Was there
always an ambition? Was there
always a kind of craving to not

06:42.900 --> 06:46.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
only get to a bigger
world, but reach people?

06:46.500 --> 06:51.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID SEDARIS: Yes. It's
all I ever wanted. It's
all I ever thought about.

06:53.533 --> 06:56.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I go on tour and I'm on
stage and the lights come up
at the end and I see those

06:56.800 --> 07:01.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
people, people say, oh, that
must be awful. You go on tour
and you go to 40 cities in

07:03.766 --> 07:08.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
41 days. And then you have
the book signing. And that's
people standing in line to say

07:10.433 --> 07:11.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
